Provisioning templates for Cisco CP Phones 78XX/88XX series with Cisco Callmanager firmware.

Those phones use cisco proprietary SIP signalling and require patched asterisk.

Details of the patch and Cisco CP phones specific at 
https://usecallmanager.nz/documentation-overview.html

Those phones doesn't work with vanilla Thirdlane PBX and use dual SIP - 5060 for regular phones 
and 5080 for Cisco CP.

This scheme requires the following changes:

------ /etc/asterisk/sip,conf ---
[general]
bindaddr=0.0.0.0
bindport=5080

#include sip_peers.include
#include sip_workers.include
#include sip_peers_cisco.include
------

File sip_peers_cisco.include is generated by /var/thirdlane_load/ciscocpe_rebuild_phones.lua

This script examine pbxconf devices and device_buttons tables and generates the following section 
for each managed Cisco CP phone:

------
; 84B8022615B2
[101]
type=friend
host=dynamic
qualify=yes
cisco_usecallmanager=yes
dndbusy=yes
subscribe=102,104,103
------

Those extra parameters activates Cisco CP specific logic for the specified SIP peer.

This way all other phones/trunks work as usual at kamailio and Cisco CP phones work directly.

This scheme is fully transparent for everybody.

